#Columbia population pyramid

subject_2010 <- load_variables(2010, "acs5/subject")
cohort_names <- c("0-4", "5-9", "10-14", "15-19",
                  "20-24", "25-29", "30-34", "35-39",
                  "40-44", "45-49", "50-54", "55-59",
                  "60-64", "65-69", "70-74", "75-79",
                  "80-84", "85+")

female_vars <- 2:19 %>%
  str_pad(2, "left", "0") %>%
  paste0("S0101_C03_0", .) %>%
  set_names(cohort_names)

male_vars <- 2:19 %>%
  str_pad(2, "left", "0") %>%
  paste0("S0101_C02_0", .) %>%
  set_names(cohort_names)

#2010
male_data_2010 <- get_acs(
  geography = "place",
  state = "MO",
  variables = male_vars,
  year = 2010
) %>% filter(grepl("Columbia", NAME)) %>% 
  mutate(NAME = str_remove(NAME, " city, Missouri")) %>% 
  mutate(sex = "Male",
         estimate = estimate * -1)


female_data_2010 <- get_acs(
  geography = "place",
  state = "MO",
  variables = female_vars,
  year = 2010
) %>% filter(grepl("Columbia", NAME)) %>% 
  mutate(NAME = str_remove(NAME, " city, Missouri")) %>% 
  mutate(sex = "Female")

pyramid_2010 <- bind_rows(male_data_2010, female_data_2010)%>%
  mutate(variable = factor(variable, levels = cohort_names))
ggplot(pyramid_2010, 
       aes(x = estimate, 
           y = variable, 
           fill = sex)) + 
  geom_col(width = 0.95, alpha = 0.75) + 
  theme_minimal(base_size = 16) + 
  scale_x_continuous(labels = function(x) paste0(abs(x / 1000), "k")) + 
  scale_fill_manual(values = c("#000000", "#F1B82D")) + 
  labs(x = "", 
       y = "ACS estimate", 
       title = "2010 Population structure in Columbia, Missouri", 
       fill = "", 
       caption = "Data source: 2006-2010 ACS & tidycensus R package")

ggsave(filename = "pyramid2010.png",
       path = "maps",
       width = 8,
       height = 5,
       units = "in",
       dpi = 300)

#Median income

years <- c(2010:2020)

median_income <- map_dfr(years, function(year) {
  get_acs(
  geography = "place",
  variables = c(median_income = "B19013_001"),
  state = "MO",
  year = year) %>% 
    mutate(year = year)
})
  
columbia_median_income <- median_income %>% filter(grepl("Columbia", NAME))

write_csv(columbia_median_income, "data/columbia_median_income.csv")

#Poverty rate

#Missouri's cities poverty rate in 2020: to see where Columbia is

#B17010_002: Estimate!!Total:!!Income in the past 12 months below poverty level (Concept: POVERTY STATUS IN THE PAST 12 MONTHS OF FAMILIES BY FAMILY TYPE BY PRESENCE OF RELATED CHILDREN UNDER 18 YEARS BY AGE OF RELATED CHILDREN)

#B17010_001: Estimate!!Total: (Concept: POVERTY STATUS IN THE PAST 12 MONTHS OF FAMILIES BY FAMILY TYPE BY PRESENCE OF RELATED CHILDREN UNDER 18 YEARS BY AGE OF RELATED CHILDREN)

mo_poverty <- get_acs(
  geography = "place",
  variables = c(poverty_num = "B17010_002",
                poverty_denom = "B17010_001"),
  state = "MO",
  year = 2020,
  output = "wide"
) %>% filter(grepl("city", NAME)) %>% 
  mutate(percent = (poverty_numE/poverty_denomE)*100) %>% 
  arrange(desc(percent))

#Because there are alot of small cities, I'll filter places where poverty_denomE is bigger than 20,000
mo_bigcity_poverty_2020 <- mo_poverty %>% filter(poverty_denomE > 20000)

#Columbia is 3/8 among big cities in Missouri in term of lowest poverty percent (8.5%)

years <- c(2010:2018)

education1 <- map_dfr(years, function(year) {
  get_acs(
    geography = "place",
    variables = c(percent = "DP02_0067P"),
    state = "MO",
    year = year
  ) %>% mutate(year = year)
})

columbia_education1 <- education1 %>% filter(grepl("Columbia", NAME))

year1 <- c(2019:2020)

education2 <- map_dfr(year1, function(year) {
  get_acs(
    geography = "place",
    variables = c(percent = "DP02_0068P"),
    state = "MO",
    year = year
  ) %>% mutate(year = year)
})

columbia_education2 <- education2 %>% filter(grepl("Columbia", NAME))

#MO top 20 counties with highest income

mo_income_county <- get_acs(
  geography = "county",
  variables = "B19013_001",
  state = "MO",
  year = 2020,
  geometry = TRUE
) %>% mutate(NAME = str_remove(NAME, " County, Missouri"))

mo_income_county <- mo_income_county %>% arrange(desc(estimate))

mo_top20 <- mo_income_county %>% filter(estimate > 58426)
mo_map <- ggplot(mo_top20, aes(fill = estimate)) +
  geom_sf_interactive(aes(data_id = GEOID)) +
  scale_fill_distiller(palette = "Greens",
                       direction = 1,
                       guide = "none") +
  theme_void()

mo_plot <- ggplot(mo_top20, aes(x = estimate, y = reorder(NAME, estimate), fill = estimate)) +
  geom_errorbarh(aes(xmin = estimate - moe, xmax = estimate + moe)) +
  geom_point_interactive(color = "black", size = 4, shape = 21,
                         aes(data_id = GEOID)) +
  scale_fill_distiller(palette = "Greens", direction = 1,
                       labels = scales::dollar) +
  scale_x_continuous(labels = scales::dollar) +
  labs(title = "Top 20 household income by county in Missouri",
       subtitle = "2016 - 2020 American Community Survey",
       y = "",
       x = "ACS estimate (bars represent margin of error)",
       fill = "ACS estimate") +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 14)

girafe(ggobj = mo_map + mo_plot, width_svg = 10, height_svg = 5) %>% 
  girafe_options(opts_hover(css = "fill:cyan;"))

groups <- c("Hispanic" = "hispanic",
            "White" = "white",
            "Black" = "black",
            "Native American" = "native",
            "Asian" = "asian")

ui <- fluidPage(
  sidebarLayout(
    sidebarPanel(
      selectInput(
        inputId = "group",
        label = "Select a group to map",
        choices = groups
      )
    ),
    mainPanel(
      leafletOutput("map", height = "600")
    )
  )
)

server <- function(input, output) {
  
  # Reactive function that filters for the selected group in the drop-down menu
  group_to_map <- reactive({
    filter(twin_cities_race, variable == input$group)
  })
  
  # Initialize the map object, centered on the Minneapolis-St. Paul area
  output$map <- renderLeaflet({

    leaflet(options = leafletOptions(zoomControl = FALSE)) %>%
      addProviderTiles(providers$Stamen.TonerLite) %>%
      setView(lng = -93.21,
              lat = 44.98,
              zoom = 8.5)

  })
  
  observeEvent(input$group, {
    
    pal <- colorNumeric("viridis", group_to_map()$estimate)
    
    leafletProxy("map") %>%
      clearShapes() %>%
      clearControls() %>%
      addPolygons(data = group_to_map(),
                  color = ~pal(estimate),
                  weight = 0.5,
                  fillOpacity = 0.5,
                  smoothFactor = 0.2,
                  label = ~estimate) %>%
      addLegend(
        position = "bottomright",
        pal = pal,
        values = group_to_map()$estimate,
        title = "% of population"
      )
  })
  
}

shinyApp(ui = ui, server = server)
